title: CarParts.com: Q2 Earnings Snapshot
snippet: TORRANCE, Calif. (AP) — TORRANCE, Calif. (AP) — CarParts.com, Inc. (PRTS) on Tuesday reported a loss of $12.7 million in its second quarter. On a per-share basis, the Torrance, California-based company said it had a loss of 23 cents. The online auto parts retailer posted revenue of $151.9 million in the period.
